You will be supporting the HR Business Partner team in the areas of staff confirmation, new hire on-boarding, manpower staffing and trending, staff development, performance management, re-employment and assist recruitment team where necessary. Your role will include consolidating and analysing the needs in these areas for timely updates and analysis. You will also be supporting the on-going digitisation efforts.

Requirements
• IT savvy and skilful with Word, Excel and Powerpoint tools
• Good interpersonal and communication skills, with confidence in interacting with senior management
• Able to analyse and present data in reports
• Qualification in Human Resource, Business Administration or Business related disciplines
